headline.main: VIRU BAY IS SEIZED; Harbor South of Air Base at Munda Taken in Landing Operation

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, July 1 -- The first great air battle reported in the new battle of the south and southwest Pacific resulted in the destruction of at least sixty-five out of 110 Japanese planes that attempted to interfere with the landing of United States forces at Rendova Island, the Navy reported today.
abstract: Believed safe after USS McCawley sinking
